ave two godsons called Toivo so it has special meaning for me.</p>\n<p>Toivo is a beautiful templatefor business, personal, portfolio or blog sites. It has powerful Front Page template where you can show your important content, portfolio, testimonials and Callout links.</p>\n<p>Check out the <a href=\"https://foxland.foxnet.fi/demo/toivo/\">demo site to see Toivo in action</a>.</p>\n<h2>Accessible WordPress theme</h2>\n<p>It&#8217;s hard to say how long I have build this one, at least couple of months. In the process I&#8217;ve been learning more and more about accessibility in WordPress themes and I consider this theme also <strong>accessibility-ready</strong>. If theme is accepted in WordPress.com it will also get official check for accessibility. I&#8217;ll be writing article about learningaccessibility in WordPress themes soon.</p>\n<p>Edit: Toivo got official<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/themes/tags/accessibility-ready/\">accessibility-ready</a> tag and I also wrote an article <a href=\"https://poststatus.com/how-to-create-accessible-wordpress-themes/\">How to create better, more accessible WordPress themes</a>.</p>\n<h2>Gallery</h2>\n<p>[envira-gallery id=&#8221;3074&#8243;]</p>\n<h2>Features</h2>\n<p>I&#8217;m not the biggest fan of lot&#8217;s of shiny features in a theme, like build in sliders. But in the same time not all themes should be minimalistic blogging themes. With Toivo I&#8217;ll try to combine bothbeautiful blogging template and powerful Front Page and Child Page templates for business types of sites. Theme already supports all the WordPress build in features like Custom Header or Background. What else is under the hood?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Powerful <a href=\"https://foxland.foxnet.fi/demo/toivo/\">Front Page Template</a>. You can also Feature only Child Pages in <a href=\"https://foxland.foxnet.fi/demo/toivo/child-pages/\">Child Page Template</a>. There are some cool settings in the Customizer for Front Page Template.\n<ul>\n<li>Set Callout text and link at the top or bottom of the page.</li>\n<li>You can add Callout Image at the bottom of the page.</li>\n<li>By default <strong>Featured Content</strong> is Child Pages of the front page. You can change that to Blog posts or Portfolios from the Customizer.</li>\n<li>You can show (or hide) your testimonials after or before featured content.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>You can also add <strong>background image</strong> in the Footer sidebar, not just in the Header. In both places you can <strong>set the color and it&#8217;s opacity</strong> in the Customizer.</li>\n<li>By default layout is one columns but you can change it to two columns layout in the Customizer. Content on the left or right with sidebar.</li>\n<li>Toivo have three menus: Top, Social for your social links and Primary menu. It also has support for <strong>menu item descriptions</strong>.</li>\n<li>Change <a href=\"https://foxland.foxnet.fi/demo/toivo/portfolio/\">Portfolio archive page</a> title anddescription.</li>\n<li>Theme alsosupports right to left languagesand <a href=\"http://schema.org/\">Schema.org</a> microdata.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>The Customizer Gallery</h2>\n<p>[envira-gallery id=&#8221;3113&#8243;]</p>\n<h2>Power up your site with Jetpack</h2>\n<p>Lot&#8217;s of people don&#8217;t like Jetpack, I know I didn&#8217;t. But in a way I have changed my mind. We get along pretty well at the moment and it has lot&#8217;s of great tools for users.</p>\n<p>Theme works just fine on its own but if you want more features install and activate <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/jetpack/\">Jetpack</a> Plugin. After that you get these features.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Upload your logo.</li>\n<li>Show your <a href=\"https://foxland.foxnet.fi/demo/toivo/testimonial/\">testimonials</a>.</li>\n<li>Show your <a href=\"https://foxland.foxnet.fi/demo/toivo/portfolio/\">portfolios</a>.</li>\n<li>Add infinite scroll in your blog.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Theme review</h2>\n<p>Toivo have been reviewed by Justin Tadlock and Emil